<normalizedToken id="748E2D9AA4FBE54424834FCDA1F8957D" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(n = 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6C0E603D848ACD288BD6664DA6941EEF" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="29BE94F7CE43D61A26C846EDCC96056E" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B4584E406A8581D824951F155BB149E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">The species is known from its type locality only.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="66832AE23021B409F3F7961973AA0F50" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph id="13F91C055DCFA7A68E23F7F25E53442B" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F4B9BF410C88832BFB774B406EE119B" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName id="AF7A8657E5B91EB3EB88FDC294260CD4" authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Stoch &amp; Mazzini" authorityYear="2022" class="Ostracoda" family="Loxoconchidae" genus="Pseudolimnocythere" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudolimnocythere abdita" order="Harpacticoida" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdita">
<emphasis id="DB49D31DAE5D9722B6D4B0C0D4B1A13F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Pseudolimnocythere abdita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. differs from other described living or subfossil species of the genus with 
<normalizedToken id="8D19343BFE7FEA9ABAF5FE5452DD9007" originalValue="“sloping”">&quot;sloping&quot;</normalizedToken>
valves (see below) in its intermediate size, being larger than 
<taxonomicName id="88C432BC065EF1FB8DF921C112ED01B3" class="Charophyceae" family="Characeae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P." order="Charales" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Charophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0DAAD1CEB4558DF459C7736CDC4CE066" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">P.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. sensu Schornikov, 2013 (c. 0.25 mm) and 
<taxonomicName id="726569AA710509C405BE6449A6EBC501" class="Charophyceae" family="Characeae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P." order="Charales" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Charophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EC0C0A0B99B397899CBEB1565D4997EF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">P.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 
<bibRefCitation id="FCCCDBD1CB4E846F18D4E8C9F1E1C1FE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5038/1827-806X.50.1.2342" author="Montanari, A" journalOrPublisher="International Journal of Speleology" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 14" refId="B51" refString="Montanari, A, Cerveau, N, Fiasca, B, Flot, JF, Galassi, D, Mainiero, M, McGee, D, Namiotko, T, Recanatini, S, Stoch, F, 2021. Stygobitic crustaceans in an anchialine cave with an archeological heritage at Vodeni Rat (Island of Sveti Klement, Hvar, Croatia). International Journal of Speleology 50: 1 - 14, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5038/1827-806X.50.1.2342" title="Stygobitic crustaceans in an anchialine cave with an archeological heritage at Vodeni Rat (Island of Sveti Klement, Hvar, Croatia)." url="https://doi.org/10.5038/1827-806X.50.1.2342" volume="50" year="2021">Montanari et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
(c. 0.28 mm), and shorter than 
<taxonomicName id="E8452682ABBD686FE4D164D058D90E09" class="Charophyceae" family="Characeae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P." order="Charales" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Charophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D3A6DB7CF0027117B39439B1CC93C521" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">P.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 
<bibRefCitation id="98ED18ACFF1BE0DAF44496A1B3C263CA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.4311/2011PA0230" author="Peterson, DE" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Cave and Karst Studies" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" pagination="12 - 27" refId="B55" refString="Peterson, DE, Finger, KL, Iepure, S, Mariani, S, Montanari, A, Namiotko, T, 2013. Ostracod assemblages in the Frasassi Caves and adjacent sulfidic spring and Sentino River in the northeastern Apennines of Italy. Journal of Cave and Karst Studies 75: 12 - 27, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4311/2011PA0230" title="Ostracod assemblages in the Frasassi Caves and adjacent sulfidic spring and Sentino River in the northeastern Apennines of Italy." url="https://doi.org/10.4311/2011PA0230" volume="75" year="2013">Peterson et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
(c. 0.35 mm), and 
<taxonomicName id="0875AA92C693EA74C30351D504F1A627" class="Charophyceae" family="Characeae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P." order="Charales" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Charophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEA692AF4C859E03481456877B2255E0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">P.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 
<bibRefCitation id="12FB27671F2A8CEC6CD07B409FB33378" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1163/26660644-05002001" author="Danielopol, DL" journalOrPublisher="Bijdragen tot de Dierkunde" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" pagination="243 - 291" refId="B18" refString="Danielopol, DL, 1980. An essay to assess the age of the freshwater interstitial ostracods of Europe. Bijdragen tot de Dierkunde 50: 243 - 291, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1163/26660644-05002001" title="An essay to assess the age of the freshwater interstitial ostracods of Europe." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/26660644-05002001" volume="50" year="1980">Danielopol 1980</bibRefCitation>
(0.34-0.36 mm). For all these species, only the morphology of the valves is known, therefore a comparison with the soft parts of 
<taxonomicName id="EDF939735369244193560B9B4847A718" class="Charophyceae" family="Characeae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. abdita" order="Charales" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="abdita">
<emphasis id="158E924220ED3350404E46FD703EE124" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">P. abdita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is not possible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA9FAF0CFE08EBC7EBF15EDEA23052EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="4222A410F5FB386A89E7EEE202D2B60C" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="85EA6D65D6D1671614C4E54318B22DB9" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName id="6E0A58D4D38BCCF11223C86828AC9F59" authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Stoch &amp; Mazzini" authorityYear="2022" class="Ostracoda" family="Loxoconchidae" genus="Pseudolimnocythere" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudolimnocythere abdita" order="Harpacticoida" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdita">
<emphasis id="A47DF0F3EEC59D4DDB374176BA60E4E9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Pseudolimnocythere abdita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is here formally described, in spite of the fact that a single female specimen was available. We have decided to do this for the following reasons:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="79CF7B93FC8E1AB350BFEE79ACD07457" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">both valve and soft features are described, allowing us to clearly distinguish the new species from its congenerics;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="473203FDDCDE7521F4589723EC39AED9" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">
so far only two other living species are known for the genus 
<taxonomicName id="47E1E93633D426BD97A4044C09D889F6" authorityName="Klie" authorityYear="1938" class="Ostracoda" family="Loxoconchidae" genus="Pseudolimnocythere" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudolimnocythere" order="Harpacticoida" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D1304154CBB21D8AAF6100E4CAD3E55D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Pseudolimnocythere</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is of particular importance to better understand the origin, phylogenetic affinities and distribution of non-marine representatives of the family Loxoconchidae;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="72E5543CBAE29270C632ABAC529E0344" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">the habitat from which the species was collected strikingly differs from those of other living congeners (see below);</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C9F71DCC7DE04D69CF6C742FAA226D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">further samplings performed in the type locality and surrounding spring areas did not yield additional specimens.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D5B59F3854BD3D56A3499CAA89BFF506" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">
We are thus confident that 
<taxonomicName id="A69188483AC002C41A54E88D684A95FB" authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Stoch &amp; Mazzini" authorityYear="2022" class="Ostracoda" family="Loxoconchidae" genus="Pseudolimnocythere" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudolimnocythere abdita" order="Harpacticoida" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdita">
<emphasis id="692FA6058F79F4630580501AC81079DE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Pseudolimnocythere abdita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be unambiguously identified on the characters presented here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
